<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="toggleAllFolders();">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;open/close all folders&nbsp; </div><p></p><h1> LG Radgrid "Hitotsuyanagi-tai"</h1><p>The focal Legion of the <em>BOUQUET</em> TV anime, <em>League of Gardens</em>, and the first novel. Comprised of leader Hitotsuyanagi Riri, her Schutzengel Shirai Yuyu, Yuyu's former legion-mate Yoshimura Thi Mai, and other first-years recruited by Riri.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder0');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In General&nbsp;</div><div id="folder0" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BunnyEarsLawyer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BunnyEarsLawyer">Bunny-Ears Lawyer</a>: They've all got their eccentricities but are a nonetheless highly effective, coordinated Legion.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder1');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hitotsuyanagi Riri&nbsp;</div><div id="folder1" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="quoteright" style="width:350px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:175.14%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/lily_hitosuyanagi_28anime29.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/lily_hitosuyanagi_28anime29.png" width="350" height="613"></div></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:350px;">Snowflake</div><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 15 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> June 19 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> A <br><strong>Height/Weight:</strong> 156cm/49kg <br><strong>Three sizes:</strong> B80/W55/H73 <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> Physical activity, all sports, collecting crystals <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> Ramune juice, junk food <br><strong>Dislikes:</strong> Insects <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> Gungnir, Brionac <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> Charisma <br><strong>Position:</strong> BZ <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Akao Hikaru (Japanese), <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/SarahWiedenheft" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/SarahWiedenheft">Sarah Wiedenheft</a> (English)</div><p>Inspired to become a Lily when she was rescued by Yuyu two years ago during the Withdrawal from Koshu, she enrolled to Yurigaoka after being placed on its entrance waitlist. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllLovingHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllLovingHero">Friendly to everyone</a>, she has a talent for winning over those around her. Her belief that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PluckyGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PluckyGirl">"you can succeed if you stand up to fear of failure"</a> can drive her to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Determinator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Determinator">push herself too far</a>.</p><hr><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationalWimp" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationalWimp">Adaptational Wimp</a>: The anime's depiction of Riri leaves out many events exemplifying her heroic or positive traits present in other media, such as her repeatedly practicing late into the night to improve her combat ability, or her attempts at reaching out to asocial characters like Yujia and Tazusa. Even the formation of Hitotsuyanagi-tai, which in the anime was a task Yuyu gave to her because it seemed as though Riri was slacking off, was originally something <em>Riri</em> (with some encouragement) came up with in the novel and in <em>League of Gardens</em> so that Yuyu would have a Legion she could belong to.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CooldownHug" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CooldownHug">Cooldown Hug</a>: Frequently applied to Yuyu by Riri when Yuyu's Lunatic Trancer-induced rampages get the better of her. Often accompanied by Riri calling out some variant of, "[Yuyu-sama/Onee-sama], please, listen to my voice."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenTheGirlsWantHer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvenTheGirlsWantHer">Even the Girls Want Her</a>: Considering the cast is mostly girls, there are several girls who have quite an interest in her, including Kaede and Araya.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroesPreferSwords" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroesPreferSwords">Heroes Prefer Swords</a>: While her CHARM also has an assault rifle component, she uses the blade most often in battle and only shoots for suppressing fire or while she's getting in melee range. Ironically, while she tends to use the Gungnir like a sword, it is (like its namesake) a "lance" model CHARM better suited for thrusting.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IOweYouMyLife" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IOweYouMyLife">I Owe You My Life</a>: Wants to become a Lily because Yuyu saved her life. A large part of Riri's motivations stems from wanting to help others, Yuyu included, like how Yuyu had saved her back then.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItWasAGift" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItWasAGift">It Was a Gift</a>: The Brionac she wields in the "Hitotsuyanagi Riri version 2.0" unit, and her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProtectiveCharm" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProtectiveCharm">four-leaf clover accessory</a>, are both gifts from Yuyu.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LivingEmotionalCrutch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LivingEmotionalCrutch">Living Emotional Crutch</a>: For Yuyu, and to a smaller extent, for Tazusa. In Yuyu's case, this carries over into combat as well, due to how Riri's Charisma complements Yuyu's Lunatic Trancer.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLoad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLoad">The Load</a>: Starts off a bit like one in the beginning, as several of her classmates already had experience with practice combat, or even had seen actual battle. Her storyline and motivations in <em>The Fateful Gift</em> mostly revolve around Riri's desire to support Yuyu better, both in and out of battle.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagneticHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagneticHero">Magnetic Hero</a>: For someone who's so inexperienced, socially awkward, and only got into the school by lucking out with the wait-list, she's quite skilled at enlisting allies for her Legion and becoming rather popular with her schoolmates. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">In the anime, Matsuri suggests that it may be the effects of Riri's Charisma at work. Since the anime removes or changes the reasons that Riri's friends were drawn to her in other media, whether Matsuri's hypothesis is accurate or otherwise remains to be seen.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunnyName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunnyName">Punny Name</a>: "Riri" is very similar to the Japanese pronunciation of the English word "Lily". She points this out in the first anime episode, saying how people used to tease her because of it. Her <a class="urllink" href="https://twitter.com/assaultlily_lb/status/1326449592670384128">self-introduction<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> for <em>Last Bullet</em> also makes reference to this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RookieRedRanger" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RookieRedRanger">Rookie Red Ranger</a>: Despite her being a new recruit and repeatedly insisting that Hitotsuyanagi-tai is "[Yuyu]'s Legion," everybody else considers Riri the team leader.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RoseHairedSweetie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RoseHairedSweetie">Rose-Haired Sweetie</a>: One of the kindest characters you'll meet. She's sweet and kind to everyone.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperReflexes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperReflexes">Super Reflexes</a>: Riri has been shown to instinctively react quickly to certain situations, whether it's stopping Kaede from interfering with a fight to actually saving her life during the battle against the Huge twice in episode 1 of the anime. Yuyu was somewhat convinced that the actually inexperienced Riri had some combat experience because of this. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationExplanationExtrication" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationExplanationExtrication">In the anime, Riri's athleticism and interest in sports is never brought up onscreen</a>, whereas it is implied or stated outright in other media.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood">Trademark Favorite Food</a>: Ramune and anything ramune-flavored.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder2');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Shirai Yuyu&nbsp;</div><div id="folder2" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="quoteright" style="width:350px;"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/yuyu_shirai_28anime29_3.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/yuyu_shirai_28anime29_3.png"></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:350px;">Lunatic Angel</div><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 16 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> April 12 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> O (profile), A (<em>Last Bullet</em>) <br><strong>Height/Weight:</strong> 163cm/48kg <br><strong>Three sizes:</strong> B90/W59/H90 <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> Reading, watching shows <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> Black tea, sandwiches <br><strong>Dislikes:</strong> Vulgar and crude things <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> D&aacute;insleif, Brionac, Gram <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> Lunatic Trancer <br><strong>Position:</strong> AZ <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Natsuyoshi Yuko (Japanese), <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LindsaySeidel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LindsaySeidel">Lindsay Seidel</a> (English)</div><p>A Lily with capabilities on the level of representing Yurigaoka. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStoic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStoic">She has a stoic personality that makes her impose high standards on herself</a>. Due to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiedInYourArmsTonight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DiedInYourArmsTonight">a certain incident</a>, she has kept herself at a distance from others.</p><hr><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAce" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAce">The Ace</a>: Considered to be one of the strongest Lilies in Yurigaoka. There's a reason why Riri looks up to her.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadPowersGoodPeople" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadPowersGoodPeople">Bad Powers, Good People</a>: Lunatic Trancer sends Yuyu into an <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage">Unstoppable Rage</a> that makes her as dangerous to her allies as she is a threat against their foes. Like other Lunatic Trancer users in the series, the mental and emotional stress she is under when activating her Rare Skill eases when in the presence of somebody she <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LivingEmotionalCrutch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LivingEmotionalCrutch">feels she can depend on</a> &mdash; Misuzu before her death, and afterwards, Riri. Beneath her aloof facade, Yuyu cares deeply for her few friends, and being one of the only two second-years in Hitotsuyanagi-tai, guides along her underclassmen on and off the field.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrokenPedestal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrokenPedestal">Broken Pedestal</a>: In the anime, after becoming Riri's Schutzengel, Yuyu is trying to make herself look like one to Riri, and at the end of episode 2, she outright wants Riri to regret her decision for doing so. Ironically, her counterparts in the novels and stage plays are terrified of disappointing Riri and worry that she is not being a good role model to her. By the later anime episodes, when Yuyu has warmed up to Riri, the viewer comes to see that she is doing her best to avert the trope.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DefrostingIceQueen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DefrostingIceQueen">Defrosting Ice Queen</a>: Riri is slowly defrosting her, in particular, the fifth episode, where she goes out of her way to try to buy some ramune for Riri's birthday.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy">Expy</a>: The SHAFT anime makes her come off as one to other <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AloofDarkHairedGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AloofDarkHairedGirl">Aloof Dark-Haired Girl</a> characters with SHAFT involvement in their design/production such as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PuellaMagiMadokaMagica" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PuellaMagiMadokaMagica">Homura Akemi</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MagiaRecordPuellaMagiMadokaMagicaSideStory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MagiaRecordPuellaMagiMadokaMagicaSideStory">Yachiyo Nanami</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImpossibleTask" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImpossibleTask">Impossible Task</a>: Because of Riri slacking off in episode 4, Yuyu asks Riri to form a Legion of 9 people, expecting a beginner like her to fail miserably and face reality. However, Riri ends up getting 5 girls to sign up at the end of episode 4 and then completes the task at the end of episode 5. Yuyu is quite impressed.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LonelyTogether" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LonelyTogether">Lonely Together</a>: Yuyu's Schutzengel and the girl who would have become Matsuri's Schild <a class="urllink" href="https://twitter.com/assault_lily/status/1222538184698949633">both passed away<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>, which led to Yuyu and Matsuri <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CommonalityConnection" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CommonalityConnection">spending much time together because of their shared circumstances</a> and eventually rooming together.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShellShockedVeteran" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShellShockedVeteran">Shell-Shocked Veteran</a>: Two years ago, her Schutzengel Misuzu died in battle, apparently at Yuyu's own hands. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">The truth of the matter is more complex than that, but Yuyu had suppressed her memories due to the trauma of what happened.</span> The disbandment of her Legion thereafter did nothing to help her emotional wounds. By the point Riri reunites with her at Yurigaoka, she notices how different Yuyu is compared to before.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TraumaButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TraumaButton">Trauma Button</a>: Misuzu's death and everything associated with it, particularly, Yuyu's old D&aacute;insleif that injured her. In <em>The Fateful Gift</em> and the anime, the sight of the D&aacute;insleif leaves Yuyu very shaken and bent on retrieving it.</li></ul></div><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder3');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Andou Tazusa&nbsp;</div><div id="folder3" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="quoteright" style="width:350px;"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/tazusa_ando_anime_1.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/tazusa_ando_anime_1.png"></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:350px;">Blood-spattering Lily</div><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 15 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> February 13 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> AB (profile), O (<em>Last Bullet</em>) <br><strong>Height/Weight:</strong> 158cm/49kg <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> Origami <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> Coffee <br><strong>Dislikes:</strong> Cramped rooms <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> D&aacute;insleif, Tyrfing <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> Phantasm <br><strong>Position:</strong> AZ/TZ <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Tsumugi Risa (Japanese)</div><p>A Lily with ties to G.E.H.E.N.A., a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MegaCorp" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MegaCorp">Mega-Corp</a> famous for research into the Huge. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SugarAndIcePersonality" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SugarAndIcePersonality">Although she gives off an impression of being cold due to how taciturn she is, she is kind at her core.</a></p><hr><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkAndTroubledPast" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkAndTroubledPast">Dark and Troubled Past</a>: Tazusa was orphaned as a child, sent to GEHENA where she experienced the "living hell" of the Boosted Lily experiments, and even after she was taken into Yurigaoka custody, still could not escape GEHENA's and the government's hold over her.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDogBitesBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDogBitesBack">The Dog Bites Back</a>: In <em>The Fateful Gift</em>, she has the opportunity to pay GEHENA back for all the suffering inflicted upon herself and the other Boosted Lilies, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HoistByHisOwnPetard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HoistByHisOwnPetard">using the powers she gained when experimented on by GEHENA</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment">Establishing Character Moment</a>: During her first appearance in the anime, she's shown to coldly reject Riri's invitation to join her Legion, but then she gets all excited upon seeing a cat shortly after, showing that she really likes cats, but has a distrust towards humans.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntrovertedCatPerson" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntrovertedCatPerson">Introverted Cat Person</a>: Initially not really open to many people, but she's keen on cats roaming the campus.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItsPersonal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItsPersonal">It's Personal</a>: Tazusa's reasons for going to Ludvico's aid at the start of <em>The Fateful Gift</em> boil down to concern and empathy for the Boosted Lilies there. It gets all the more personal for her after the extent of GEHENA's involvement is brought to light.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrphansOrdeal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OrphansOrdeal">Orphan's Ordeal</a>: Her father died in the war and was declared a war criminal for his actions in it. Her mother committed suicide after the family were not granted survivors' pension. Mistreated and abused from a young age, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TraumaticSuperpowerAwakening" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TraumaticSuperpowerAwakening">Tazusa's Skiller value rose sharply</a> in the meantime, and she was sent to GEHENA, where she underwent horrific human experimentation and became a Boosted Lily.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SinsOfOurFathers" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SinsOfOurFathers">Sins of Our Fathers</a>: Her father was a SDF soldier branded a war criminal. After Tazusa was engineered into a Boosted Lily, she was made to carry out dangerous anti-Huge operations for the government, with her handler/commanding officer only ever referring to her as "Andou's daughter" and not seeing her as her own person.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhoWantsToLiveForever" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhoWantsToLiveForever">Who Wants to Live Forever?</a>: Tazusa's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HealingFactor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HealingFactor">Healing Factor</a> as a Boosted Lily lets her recover much faster than a regular human, and from much worse injuries at that, so she is prone to throwing herself into dangerous situations with nary a care for her own safety. By the time of the battle at Shimo-Kitazawa, she wonders aloud whether the Huge she is up against might finally be able to kill her. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePowerOfFriendship" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThePowerOfFriendship">Befriending the rest of Hitotsuyanagi-tai has improved her outlook significantly.</a></li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder4');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Futagawa Fumi&nbsp;</div><div id="folder4" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="quoteright" style="width:350px;"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/fumi_futagawa.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/fumi_futagawa.png"></div><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 15 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> December 21 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> O <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> Reading official bulletins, camping, collecting otter merchandise, Lily otaku pursuits, reading "World Lily Graphic" magazine <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> Dagashi, gyudon <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> Gungnir <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> Taka no Me <br><strong>Position:</strong> BZ <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Nishimoto Rimi (Japanese), Suzie Yeung (English)</div><p>This "Lily otaku" possesses a broad range of knowledge in overwhelming quantity and quantity, not just regarding Lilies but also CHARMs and battle tactics. She usually is not the type to step forward, though when the topic shifts to anything Lily-related, she takes a proactive stance.</p><hr><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment">Establishing Character Moment</a>: We're introduced with her nerding out over Riri talking with Kaede along with pointing out Yuyu and Araya, knowing a lot about them.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GeekyTurnOn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GeekyTurnOn">Geeky Turn-On</a>: She gets <em>very</em> excited by anything involving Lilies, CHARMS, or combat against Huge, to the point of having a gigantic database of everything you could ever want to know about all three.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GlowingEyes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GlowingEyes">Glowing Eyes</a>: Gets these whenever she uses her Rare Skill.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagicalEye" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagicalEye">Magical Eye</a>: Her Rare Skill is a eye-related power that grants her ridiculous sight, meaning she can identify targets and movements at large distance with pinpoint precision.</li><li> Nosebleed: Has regular ones whenever she gets an overdose of anything related to Lilyss. At some point, she even stuffs her nose with tissue paper.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmartGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmartGirl">The Smart Girl</a>: May not have a lot of combat experience but she's very familiar with a lot of Lily technology.</li></ul></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder5');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Miriam Hildegard von Gropius&nbsp;</div><div id="folder5" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="quoteright" style="width:349px;"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/miliam_gropius_2.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/miliam_gropius_2.png"></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:349px;">Der Sturm</div><div c