Nicknamer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheNicknamer">The Nicknamer</a>: She frequently refers to her classmates with childish nicknames like "Fumin" and "Wang-Wang".</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TerribleArtist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TerribleArtist">Terrible Artist</a>: Mai enjoys drawing, but what she draws is... <a class="urllink" href="https://twitter.com/assault_lily/status/1275442998214447106">avant garde<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WalkonWater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WalkonWater">Walkon Water</a>: She has never done, but it seems to be at least possible if you use enough energy.</li></ul></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder10');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Yuri Hitotsuyanagi&nbsp;</div><div id="folder10" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><p>An unknown girl who was found after a fight against a Huge in the anime. She takes an attachment to Riri and almost treats her as a parent.</p><hr><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtificialHuman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtificialHuman">Artificial Human</a>: Even though she's revealed to have DNA of a normal human, it's <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">strongly implied she was created from the stem cells of a Huge as a synthetic Lily as an experiment of G.E.H.E.N.A.</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FamousLastWords" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FamousLastWords">Famous Last Words</a>: "Riri ... I did it." Said after she managed to single-handedly destroy a Huge nest <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">as it exploded, killing her too</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdentityAmnesia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdentityAmnesia">Identity Amnesia</a>: She has no idea who she is. Riri names her "Yuri", after her and Yuyu's <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PortmanteauCoupleName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PortmanteauCoupleName">Portmanteau Couple Name</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HasTwoMommies" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HasTwoMommies">Has Two Mommies</a>: In a way, Riri and Yuyu are considered her "parents".</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice">Heroic Sacrifice</a>: Fights and defeats a very powerful Huge with relative ease <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">at the cost of her own life</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RidiculouslyAverageGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RidiculouslyAverageGuy">Ridiculously Average Guy</a>: At least genetically speaking, it is what first makes people notice the possibility <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">that she is related to the Huge.</span> Her genetics are just too average to be normal.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StoryBreakerPower" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StoryBreakerPower">Story-Breaker Power</a>: As a <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Synethetic Lily</span>, she's really fast and powerful. She was able to easily take out a Huge nest too. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Her being powerful did might have been why she had to be taken out after three episodes ...</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WalkingSpoiler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WalkingSpoiler">Walking Spoiler</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStinger" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStinger">The Stinger</a> for Episode 8 along with the entirety of Episode 9 <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">reveal her connections as a Synthetic Lily created from Huge stem cells along with her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice">Heroic Sacrifice</a> while fighting a Huge herself</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YankTheDogsChain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YankTheDogsChain">Yank the Dog's Chain</a>: Episode 9 had the government place an arrest order on Riri for refusing to give Yuri up due to her connections with the Huge. However, once Moyu and the Acting Chairman managed to convince the government to rescind said arrest order, a Huge attacked and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Yuri took on the Huge herself at the cost of her own life</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WalkonWater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WalkonWater">Walkon Water</a>: Combines the Shukuchi high speed movement skill and Miriam's Phase Transcendence skill to run on water.</li></ul></div><p></p><h1> Yurigaoka "Arsenal Division"</h1><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder11');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mashima Moyu&nbsp;</div><div id="folder11" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 16 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> ? <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> ? <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> ? <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> ? <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Inori Minase (Japanese), Madeleine Morris (English)</div><p>A member of the Arsenal Division specializing in repair, maintentance and production of Charms. She is something of a airhead but a hardworking young woman. It appears like she knows something about Yuyu's past and why she has switch to using a different Charm, but refuses to give details since it is a private matter.</p><hr><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Meganekko" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Meganekko">Meganekko</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBlacksmith" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBlacksmith">The Blacksmith</a>: Whereas Miriam is more active as a Lily and a member of the Arsenal Division, Moyu seems to focus mostly on the production, repair and research into Charms.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheNicknamer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheNicknamer">The Nicknamer</a>: Gave Miriam the nikname "Gropi" and named her robot for the exhibition match "Mecha Rumpelstilzchen" of all things.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder12');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hasebe Toka&nbsp;</div><div id="folder12" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">A green haired Lily in the Arsenal Division that shows off an experimental new Charm called Vampyr during episode 8 of the anime.<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe">Shock and Awe</a>: The experimental Charm she shows off looks like a mechanical kite that shoots lightning at targets.</li></ul><p></p></div><p></p><h1> LG Reinleif "W.E.T.P."</h1><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder13');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Rokkaku Shiori&nbsp;</div><div id="folder13" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="quoteright" style="width:350px;"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/shiori_rokkaku.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/shiori_rokkaku.png"></div><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 15 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> April 15 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> O <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> ? <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> Fudokenhime <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> Circlet Bless <br><strong>Position:</strong> ? <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Rie Takahashi (Japanese), Katelyn Barr (English)</div><hr>She has a careless and gentle personality, but has an indomitable nature that never gives up.<p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DemotedToExtra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DemotedToExtra">Demoted to Extra</a>: Isn't as notable in the anime as compared to other media, instead as appearing as a rather helpful character to the other students.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Determinator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Determinator">Determinator</a>: Has been determined to not give up, as explained in her character bio.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DualWielding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DualWielding">Dual Wielding</a>: Its basically her superpower, her Circlet Bless ability lets her use two Charms at once.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlishPigtails" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlishPigtails">Girlish Pigtails</a>: Sports a pair of normal looking pigtails which are quite distinct compared to other characters.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiotHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiotHair">Idiot Hair</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NiceGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NiceGirl">Nice Girl</a>: Wishes Riri and Fumi the best of luck in forming a great legion, even if she cannot join herself.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NumberTwo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NumberTwo">Number Two</a>: Essentially why she cannot join Ruri's legion.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron">Red Baron</a>: Is called the "Unshakable Sword Princess" according to Fumi.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoundThatWillNotHeal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoundThatWillNotHeal">Wound That Will Not Heal</a>: Has an old injury that caused her to lose feeling in her left arm, which is her dominant one.</li></ul></div><p></p><h1> LG Lohengrin</h1><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder14');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sejima Hiromu&nbsp;</div><div id="folder14" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlishPigtails" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlishPigtails">Girlish Pigtails</a></li></ul></div><p></p><h1> LG Alfheim "Ichibantai"</h1>The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LegacyCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LegacyCharacter">second Legion</a> to bear the Alfheim name, led by original Alfheim member Amano Soraha, taking over leadership from Ichibantai's Tanaka Ichi.<div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder15');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Endou Araya&nbsp;</div><div id="folder15" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><h3> <strong>Voiced by:</strong> Akira Sekine (Japanese)</h3><div class="quoteright" style="width:206px;"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/araya_endo_anime.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/araya_endo_anime.png"></div><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnAxeToGrind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnAxeToGrind">An Axe to Grind</a>: Her CHARMS is an ax. We see her pull it out in the first episode.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatSmile" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatSmile">Cat Smile</a>: Like Miriam, she has one, but hers is far more noticeable.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DepravedBisexual" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DepravedBisexual">Depraved Bisexual</a>: Has been confirmed to be bisexual by the creators, and her attitude and actions towards Riri (after she helped defeat a Huge in the first episode) can come off as quite seductive. Kaede is usually there to stop her before she gets too rough though.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment">Establishing Character Moment</a>: The moment we see her in the first episode, she tries to make a scene and try to start a fight with Yuyu, letting viewers know she's quite the showoff.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheWorfEffect" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheWorfEffect">The Worf Effect</a>: She and the Alfeim Legion fight against a Huge in Episode 6 and they demonstrate their Neunwelt Tactic ... and unfortunately, the fact their tactic didn't completely defeat said Huge, forcing them to retreat.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder16');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Amano Soraha&nbsp;</div><div id="folder16" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 16 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> October 27 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> O <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> ? <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> Gram <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> Heliosphere <br><strong>Position:</strong> ? <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Minami Tsuda (Japanese), Marissa Lenti (English)</div><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiotHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiotHair">Idiot Hair</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WreckedWeapon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WreckedWeapon">Wrecked Weapon</a>: When the Huge in Episode 6 blocks the Neunwelt bullet, she cracks the barrier while breaking her weapon. Sadly it doesn't actually kill the monster.</li></ul><p></p></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder17');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Egawa Kusumi&nbsp;</div><div id="folder17" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 15 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> March 27 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> AB <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> ? <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> Asterion <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> Phantasm <br><strong>Position:</strong> ? <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Sayaka Harada (Japanese), Meg Mcclain (English)</div><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParasolParachute" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParasolParachute">Parasol Parachute</a>: Shows that off when rescuing Soraha from falling after she tries to finish off the Huge in episode 6.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShrinkingViolet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShrinkingViolet">Shrinking Violet</a>: Very quiet and tends to hide behind Ichi Tanaka or Soraha whenever something comes up</li></ul><p></p></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder18');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tanaka Ichi&nbsp;</div><div id="folder18" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 15 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> November 3 <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> B <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> ? <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> ? <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> World's Reason <br><strong>Position:</strong> ? <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Aya Suzaki (Japanese), Emi Lo (English)</div><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiotHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiotHair">Idiot Hair</a></li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder19');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Bansh&#333;ya Ena&nbsp;</div><div id="folder19" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="indent"><strong>Age:</strong> 16 <br><strong>Birthday:</strong> ? <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonalityBloodTypes">Blood type</a>:</strong> ? <br><strong>Skills/Interests:</strong> ? <br><strong>Favorite food:</strong> ? <br><strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">CHARM</a>:</strong> Gram <br><strong>Rare Skill:</strong> ? <br><strong>Position:</strong> ? <br><strong>Portrayed by:</strong> Rika Tachibana (Japanese), Brittany Lauda (English)</div><p></p></div><p></p><h1> Student Council</h1><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder20');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hata Matsuri&nbsp;</div><div id="folder20" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotSoSmallRole" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotSoSmallRole">Not-So-Small Role</a>: When we're first introduced to her, she's just shown as a roommate to Yuyu (after it was revealed the other one was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGhost" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGhost">The Ghost</a>) with no big role. However, once Yuri comes in the scene, she starts to have quite a big role, overlooking the mysterious girl.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder21');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Izue Shinobu&nbsp;</div><div id="folder21" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><p></p><ul><li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder22');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Uchida Mayuri&nbsp;</div><div id="folder22" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><p></p><ul><li></ul></div><p></p><h1> Others</h1><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder23');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Misuzu Kawazoe&nbsp;</div><div id="folder23" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><div class="quoteright" style="width:279px;"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/misuzu_kawazoe.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/misuzu_kawazoe.png"></div><p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadAllAlong" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadAllAlong">Dead All Along</a>: Is revealed to be dead at the third episode, though Yuyu is sometimes shown talking to a hallucination of her.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImpaledWithExtremePrejudice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImpaledWithExtremePrejudice">Impaled with Extreme Prejudice</a>: Was impaled by a berserk Yuyu.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmugSuper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmugSuper">Smug Super</a>: When she is talking with Yuyu, she's always shown with a smug and intrigued expression.</li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder24');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Shizu Ito&nbsp;</div><div id="folder24" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">Riri's roommate and a fellow first year student at Yurigaoka. She knows quite a bit about the Lilys within the Academy.<p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLeader" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheLeader">The Leader</a>: Not yet, but she rejects Riri when she asks her to join her legion because she already decided that she would form her own legion once she gets into high school.</li></ul><p></p></div>
